IdeaJudge is a new social platform which boosts corporate social responsibility for businesses, through innovation. Here is how brands can benefit from joining this exciting, global community. Click here to learn more about IdeaJudge. IdeaJudge is the brain child of Lourence Greyvenstein- inventor of the Quick-tie bag. But the inventor’s road to success wasn’t a quick or easy one. “The experience was a test to my perseverance and determination to succeed, and I wanted to use my experience to help other inventors.” “This is what inspired me to start IdeaJudge” said Mr Greyvenstein. When a business joins IdeaJudge, they receive a page which displays fresh ideas from inventors around the world, daily. All ideas are covered by patent applications and curated by an expert team, while viewers can easily upvote any exciting ideas which show potential. An IdeaJudge page can easily be shared by employees, customers and website visitors, to their own social networks. This highlights said business’s involvement in inspiring innovation and change- leading to a boost in brand loyalty and positive association. IdeaJudge provides a fully automated service, which kicks off once the business displays the IdeaJudge badge on their website. When clicked, this badge takes visitors to the business’s IdeaJudge page, where they can enjoy a continuous stream of new ideas. IdeaJudge provides businesses with more than just a social page – it provides an integrated marketing solution. Key benefits of an IdeaJudge membership include: IdeaJudge badge – Choose from a selection of IdeaJudge badges, and easily add it to your website using the code provided. This badge seamlessly accompanies other social platform logos, and clicking on it gives visitors access to your IdeaJudge page. Email alert service – Your page’s visitors are encouraged to subscribe to your email alert service. These emails regularly send curated ideas to subscribers, in categories of their choice and on their preferred day of the week. Your logo, business name and website link are always displayed in these email alerts. If you’d like to promote your own products or services in your emails, IdeaJudge enables you to easily upload your own ad material. The IdeaJudge business member dashboard contains an insightful Analytics feature, which gives you the ability to measure your success over time. This feature tracks and displays vital information such as how many clicks your badge has received, views and clicks on your ads, profile and website visits, and much more. Join a future of social responsibility and effortless marketing – become an IdeaJudge business member today. No credit card is needed for the 30 day trial. Don’t forget to follow IdeaJudge’s Facebook, LinkedIn and Instagram to stay up-to-date with the latest ideas that are driving social impact.